race.comment: Hard to see how they beat OBSERVER (1) off his last start effort in the G1 Caulfield Guineas. He was backed in at bigger odds there and copped huge interference, badly held up as the winner got off the fence to slice through. He's by Ghaiyyath who was world class stayer and stepping up to 2040m should pose no issue at all. He'll roll forward and with any luck early, he should be winning en route to the Derby. OPTIONS (3) is a progressive colt having won 3/4, and arguably unlucky not to win the Derby Trial two back when checked. The draw doesn't do him any favours but he's a danger. PROVIDENCE (5) was in the market in the G3 Gloaming last time and got home fairly late. He looks suited up in trip and J-Mac on helps negate the draw. O'SHEAMUS (6) was good winning at Warwick Farm last time out and while this is tougher, he has plenty of scope for improvement.
